Example data for generalized linear models

Source: R/Data.R
BinaryData.Rd

A simulated data set containing response variable, provider information and 5 covariates.

Usage

data(BinaryData)

Format

A list containing the following elements:

data

example data. Y is the response variable; Prov.ID is the center indicator (include 20 centers); Z1, ..., Z5 are 5 continuous covariates.

Y.char

variable name of the response variable.

prov.char

variable name of the provider indicator.

Z.char

variable names of covariates.

group

vector describing how the covariates are grouped.

Examples

data(BinaryData)
data <- BinaryData$data
head(data)
